$:/plugins/techlifeweb/xmlbuilder/readme.text:
This plugin will create Atom, RSS, and Sitemaps of your wiki when you build a static version of your site. It does take a little upfront set up but then should just work in the background anytime you run the Build command.

The plugin consists of the following tiddlers:

* $:/plugins/techlifeweb/xmlbuilder/atomfeed
** Contains the code to build the atom feed
* $:/plugins/techlifeweb/xmlbuilder/discoverfeed
** Contains fields you'll update in the settings
* $:/plugins/techlifeweb/xmlbuilder/readme
** This text
* $:/plugins/techlifeweb/xmlbuilder/rssfeed
** Contains the code to build the rss feed
* $:/plugins/techlifeweb/xmlbuilder/settings
** The critical settings page
* $:/plugins/techlifeweb/xmlbuilder/sitemap
** Contains the code to build the sitemap
* $:/plugins/techlifeweb/xmlbuilder/static.template.html
** Contains code for the head setion of the static.html to make your atom and rss feeds discoverable
* $:/plugins/techlifeweb/xmlbuilder/static.tiddler.html
** Contains some code to be sure your site title and subtitle are on all pages. You don't have to use this in the build command if you don't want to .

{{||$:/plugins/techlifeweb/xmlbuilder/settings}}

-----------

Next you need to edit the static section of your 


```
		"static": [
			"--rendertiddler","$:/plugins/techlifeweb/xmlbuilder/static.template.html","static.html","text/plain",
			"--rendertiddlers","[!is[system]]","$:/plugins/techlifeweb/xmlbuilder/static.tiddler.html","static","text/plain",
			"--rendertiddler","$:/core/templates/static.template.css","static/static.css","text/plain",
			"--rendertiddler","$:/plugins/techlifeweb/xmlbuilder/sitemap","sitemap.xml","text/plain",
			"--rendertiddler","$:/plugins/techlifeweb/xmlbuilder/atomfeed","atom.xml","text/plain",
			"--rendertiddler","$:/plugins/techlifeweb/xmlbuilder/rssfeed","rss.xml","text/plain"]
```

The relevant lines are in red:

[img[$:/plugins/techlifeweb/xmlbuilder/image2.png]]

-----------

Now when you run

tiddlywiki --build static

in the same directory you have static.html you will also get a sitemap.xml, atom.xml and rss.xml

--------

$:/plugins/techlifeweb/xmlbuilder/settin.text:
For the files to be built correctly you have to enter the details about your files.

Put the path to your Atom.xml file here. (e.g., ~https://techlifeweb.com/tiddlywiki/mywiki/atom.xml)<p/>
''atomfile'': <$edit-text tiddler="$:/plugins/techlifeweb/xmlbuilder/discoverfeed" field="atomfile" size=80/>

Put the path to your RSS.xml file here. (e.g., ~https://techlifeweb.com/tiddlywiki/mywiki/rss.xml)<p/>
''rssfile'': <$edit-text tiddler="$:/plugins/techlifeweb/xmlbuilder/discoverfeed" field="rssfile" size=80/>

When you build a static site it creates a static.html file. serverdomain is the location of this static.html file. Trailing "/" slash is important. (e.g., ~https://techlifeweb.com/tiddlywiki/mywiki/) <p/>
''serverdomain ''<$edit-text tiddler="$:/plugins/techlifeweb/xmlbuilder/discoverfeed" field="serverdomain" size=80/>

subfolder is the location of all the individual files Trailing "/" slash is important. (e.g. static/)<p/>
''subfolder'': <$edit-text tiddler="$:/plugins/techlifeweb/xmlbuilder/discoverfeed" field="subfolder" size=80/>
